Gall types as coded by Kopelke (1999, 2003a,b). For leaf galls, codes are as follows: RK1 = thick-walled, elongated sausage-shaped galls on the upper surface of the leaf; RK2 = thin-walled, kidney-shaped spacious galls transected horizontally by the leaf blade; RK3 = thick-walled, bean-shaped galls with a narrow cavity, transected horizontally by the leaf blade; RK4 = thin to thick-walled, pea-shaped galls at the underside of the leaf
